# Error Handling

## Never swallow exceptions silently

```python
# bad
try:
    save_progress(record)
except Exception:
    pass

# good
try:
    save_progress(record)
except Exception:
    logger.debug("Failed to save progress record", exc_info=True)
```

## Prefer narrow exception types

Use `ValueError`, `FileNotFoundError`, `RuntimeError`, `KeyError`, etc. when the failure mode is known. Reserve `except Exception` for genuinely unknown/defensive paths.

## Production-critical paths must log

Order execution, checkpoint saves, and progress tracking must log at `WARNING` or `ERROR` on failure -- never silently swallow.

## Always capture tracebacks

Use `exc_info=True` on error-level log calls:

```python
logger.error("Checkpoint save failed: %s", exc, exc_info=True)
```
